==German==

===Etymology===
[[Angst]] + [[Hase]]; From the notion that rabbits, often mistakenly called ''Hase'' (“[[hare]]”) are very fearful and flee at the first hint of danger.

===Noun===
{{de-noun-m|genitive=Angsthasen|plural=Angsthasen}}
# a [[coward]]
#: ''He, '''Angsthase'''! Traust dich wohl nicht?''

